Key Match Events: Mohamed Bayo scored in the 10th minute to give Guinea an early lead.
François Kamano received a red card in the 45'+3' minute, reducing Guinea to 10 men.
Frank Magri scored in the 51st minute to equalize for Cameroon.
Post-Match Reflections: Cameroon came from behind to share the points with 10-man Guinea in a 1-1 stalemate in the first game for both teams at the Africa Cup of Nations in Ivory Coast.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Vincent Aboubakar's injury was not as bad as first feared.
The match had an attendance of 11,271 spectators.
